dspace-development.title: Ensure that the DataSpace 2021/2022 MARC records are imported into Alma

comments.body: https://github.com/jrgriffiniii/etd-processor/pull/6 were the last modifications needed to ensure that this is functioning. I am running this now for inserting the ARKs.
https://github.com/jrgriffiniii/etd-processor/pull/7 provides a task for generating MARC record reports as well.
I have confirmed that the total number number of records for each batch matches what is expected. I am now manually ensuring that those records without matching ARKs should indeed be without ARKs.
https://dataspace.princeton.edu/handle/88435/dsp01th83m246x was not found by query due to errors arising from characters `(`, `)`, and `~` in the title.
More encoding issues arose with trying to match an ARK to https://dataspace.princeton.edu/handle/88435/dsp01pr76f6551
Search query params needed to be encapsulated with double-quotation characters in order match an ARK for "How Do States Negotiate?"
More adjustments were needed to address cases where there were multiple spaces in DataSpace where there were single spaces in the MARC records.
Major encoding conflicts arose with regards to encoding problems between the MARC records and the DataSpace metadata. There are still 2 items which I need to inspect, but this may well be resolved.

figgy.title: Support multiple PDFs in one resource
Add comments and small changes to preservation code
Add job to prune multiple preservation objects
Ensure only 1 PreservationObject is made per Resource.

comments.body:
The most recent PreservationObjects created for the same Resource resource are linked to this Coin:
https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/6c6994a7-4abd-4b6b-8488-38b128fb70c2

The PreserveResourceJob was queued 5 times in a 4 minute span.

![Screenshot 2022-12-06 at 3 52 28 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/784196/206032032-7fba5f88-ba02-4b66-9133-a1905a557c6a.png)

**Theory** A Coin is created and marked complete. Changes are made and saved multiple times before any other additional PreserveResourceJobs have completed. A new preservation object is created here on each job invocation:
https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/1c3e9ae220157e4294b7fde634e0dfec8d27f713/app/services/preserver.rb#L78

This would presume that the Coin has no member FileSets because the PreserveResourceJob is run synchronously when a Resource has members.

https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/d7d7e9bc945a4c96d483d7e6d1cc173f9fcd6c5a/app/change_set_persisters/change_set_persister/preserve_resource.rb#L20-L21
Sounds like a convincing theory!
Maybe when we queue up a PreserveResourceJob we should pass its optimistic lock token and compare before we do it?

@tpendragon Am I understanding your suggestion?

1. Pass the lock token value of the resource to be preserved as a param of in the PreserveResourceJob
1. When the job is run, compare that param value with the current value of the resource.
1. Stop the job if they don't match

Seem like a good idea, although optimistic locking is only enabled for FileSets and ResourceChargeLists. Will prevent most of the multiple PreservationObject instances, but not all.
I think they're populated on the other resources, just not verified. Worth checking? It was an implementation detail
@dependabot rebase

pulfalight.title: Searching within a collection by Box number not working

comments.body:
Sorry for the delay. I think as long as it is working as it was before let's leave the ticket open and hopefully it can get worked on during a sprint. 
The need for searching by box directly at the very least is if a researcher or staff knows exactly what box something is in but not the file name. 

I will ask one last question, is the reason that Box 40 doesn't show up in the search for C0187 is that it is listed as a range of boxes? - https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog/C0187_c68425-07869

There was a connection error during indexing last night; could that be related? https://app.honeybadger.io/projects/65922/faults/91289532/01GKMQ91MTVGMAJEHWXPM966DG#notice-params

        "resource_descriptions_uri" => "repositories/3/resource_descriptions/1712",
        "repository_id" => "publicpolicy",

There was also an error during indexing on another collection, 

        "resource_descriptions_uri" => "repositories/4/resource_descriptions/2151",
        "repository_id" => "univarchives",


We should probably reindex both of them.
Neither of these errors correspond to the collection that's got the problem, which was `repositories/4/resources/2203`
a soft reindex didn't resolve. I'll try reindexing the collection directly.

Ran the job like `AspaceIndexJob.perform_later(resource_descriptions_uri: "repositories/4/res
ource_descriptions/2203", repository_id: "univarchives")` and it looks good now.
